<paragraph id="540536C8FFF3FFE1D78F8C56FEB1F806" blockId="4.[136,1452,1871,2042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF3FFE1D78F8C56FE80F8BA" bold="true" box="[136,261,1871,1897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
—Annual, decumbent to ascending, absence of rhizomes or stolons, stems unarmed, leaves linear to linear-lanceolate, petioles not winged, not auriculate, ochreae chartaceous, brownish, the margins ciliate with bristles, inflorescences spike-like, uninterrupted, perianth 5-lobed, campanulate, perianth and peduncles eglandular, styles exserted.
</paragraph>
