<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D4358B87FBE9FF6B" author="Komarov, V. L. &amp; Grigoriev, Yu. S." box="[818,1132,158,184]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" pagination="594 - 701" refId="ref5218" refString="Komarov, V. L. &amp; Grigoriev, Yu. S. (1936) Goрit - Polygonum. In: Komarov, V. L. (Ed.) ФЛOРa СССР, vol. 5. IZdatiльсtvo Akadiмii Нauk СССР, Moscow and Saint Petersburg, pp. 594 - 701." type="book chapter" year="1936">Komarov &amp; Grigoriev 1936</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D3728B87FAE7FF6B" author="Webb, D. A. &amp; Chater, A. O." box="[1141,1378,158,184]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" pagination="76 - 80" refId="ref6570" refString="Webb, D. A. &amp; Chater, A. O. (1964) Polygonum L. In: Tutin, T. G., Heywood, V. H., Burges, N. A., Valentine, D. H., Walters, S. M. &amp; Webb, D. A. (Eds.) Flora Europaea, vol. 1. University Press, Cambridge, pp. 76 - 80." type="book chapter" year="1964">Webb &amp; Chater 1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D26B8B87FF41FF0F" author="Villar, L." pageId="7" pageNumber="67" pagination="571 - 586" refId="ref6501" refString="Villar, L. (1990) Polygonum L. In: Castroviejo, S., Lainz, M., Lopez, G., Montserrat, P., Munoz, F., Paiva, J. &amp; Villar, L. (Eds.) Flora Iberica, vol. 2. Real Jardin Botanico, Madrid, pp. 571 - 586." type="book chapter" year="1990">Villar 1990</bibRefCitation>
), and naturalised in eastern North America and 
<collectingCountry id="2CAD7658FFF0FFE2D5CB8BDBFCBEFF0F" box="[716,827,194,220]" name="Argentina" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D44F8BDBFC65FF0F" author="Fernald, M. L." box="[840,992,194,220]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" pagination="133 - 155" refId="ref4377" refString="Fernald, M. L. (1917) Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University. - New Series, no. L. Rhodora 19: 133 - 155." type="journal article" year="1917">Fernald 1917</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D4ED8BDBFB15FF0F" author="Cialdella, A. M." box="[1002,1168,194,220]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" pagination="179 - 246" refId="ref4071" refString="Cialdella, A. M. (1989) Revision de las especies argentinas de Polygonum s. l. (Polygonaceae). Darwiniana 29: 179 - 246." type="journal article" year="1989">Cialdella 1989</bibRefCitation>
). Molecular phylogenetic evidence presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D6838BFEFDFEFED3" author="Bunawan, H. &amp; Choong, C. Y. &amp; Md-Zain, B. M. &amp; Baharum, S. N. &amp; Noor, N. M." box="[388,635,230,257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" pagination="7626 - 7634" refId="ref3884" refString="Bunawan, H., Choong, C. Y., Md-Zain, B. M., Baharum, S. N. &amp; Noor, N. M. (2011) Molecular systematics of Polygonum minus Huds. based on ITS sequences. International Journal Of Molecular Sciences 12: 7626 - 7634. https: // doi. org / 10.3390 / ijms 12117626" type="journal article" year="2011">
Bunawan 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D6F38BFEFDAEFED3" box="[500,555,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">et al.</emphasis>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
suggests that the current circumscription of 
<taxonomicName id="93BA4D4BFFF0FFE2D3628BFEFB47FED3" authorityName="Opiz, Seznam Rostlin Kveteny Ceske" authorityYear="1852" baseAuthorityName="Huds." box="[1125,1218,231,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Persicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D3628BFEFB47FED3" box="[1125,1218,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">P. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not monophyletic, so that the Southeast Asian populations referred to the species could perhaps constitute a separate entity. This very interesting question demands further studies for its resolution.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="540536C8FFF0FFE2D7BA8A4BFBE6FDBA" blockId="7.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="93BA4D4BFFF0FFE2D68E8A4BFCB6FEBF" authority="(Hudson 1762: 148)" baseAuthorityName="Hudson" baseAuthorityPageNumber="148" baseAuthorityYear="1762" box="[393,819,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Polygonum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minus">
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D68E8A4BFDD5FEBF" box="[393,592,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Polygonum minus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D55A8A4BFCAEFEBF" author="Hudson, W." box="[605,811,338,364]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" refId="ref4969" refString="Hudson, W. (1762) Flora Anglica. Printed by the author, London, 506 pp." type="book" year="1762">Hudson 1762: 148</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
informed no gatherings, but gave provenance as “ 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D2508A4BFA1AFEBF" box="[1367,1439,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Anglis</emphasis>
” and “ 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D7C38A6EFE48FE43" box="[196,461,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">In the meadows beyond</emphasis>
Peterborough-house, 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D5C38A6FFC8EFE43" box="[708,779,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">and in</emphasis>
Tothil-fields, Westminster”. Moreover, the protologue gave two pre-Linnean synonyms: “ 
<taxonomicName id="93BA4D4BFFF0FFE2D6CA8A83FD64FE67" box="[461,737,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Persicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pusilla" subSpecies="repens">Persicaria pusilla repens</taxonomicName>
”, for which “ 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D4778A82FC54FE67" box="[880,977,411,437]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Ger. Em.</emphasis>
446. 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D30B8A83FBCFFE67" box="[1036,1098,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Park.</emphasis>
857. 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D3838A82FB54FE66" box="[1156,1233,411,437]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">R. Syn.</emphasis>
145.” (
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D2268A82FAC1FE67" box="[1313,1348,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">i.e.</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D2578A83FF46FE0B" author="Johnson, T." pageId="7" pageNumber="67" refId="ref5090" refString="Johnson, T. (1633) The Herball, very much enlarged and amended. A. Islip, J. Norton &amp; R. Whitakers, London, 1630 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 121658" type="book" year="1633">Johnson 1633</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D7C88AA7FE07FE0B" author="Parkinson, J." box="[207,386,446,472]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" refId="ref5863" refString="Parkinson, J. (1640) Theatrum Botanicum. Th. Cotes, London, 1755 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 152383" type="book" year="1640">Parkinson 1640</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D6898AA6FE79FE0B" author="Ray, J." box="[398,508,446,473]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" refId="ref5979" refString="Ray, J. (1724) Synopsis Methodica Stirpium Britannicarum, 3 rd ed. W. &amp; J. Innys, London, 482 pp." type="book" year="1724">Ray 1724</bibRefCitation>
) were given as references, and “ 
<taxonomicName id="93BA4D4BFFF0FFE2D46B8AA7FBA8FE0B" authorityName="Opiz, Seznam Rostlin Kveteny Ceske" authorityYear="1852" baseAuthorityName="Huds." box="[876,1069,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Persicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minor">Persicaria minor</taxonomicName>
”, for which “ 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D3C28AA7FABFFE0B" box="[1221,1338,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Bauh. pin.</emphasis>
101. 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D27D8AA6FF62FE2F" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Hiss. Ox. II. s.</emphasis>
5. 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D60E8AFAFE92FE2F" box="[265,279,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">t.</emphasis>
29. 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D6408AFBFED2FE2F" box="[327,343,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">f.</emphasis>
” (
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D6758AFAFE11FE2F" box="[370,404,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">i.e.</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D6A68AFBFDB6FE2F" author="Bauhin, G." box="[417,563,482,508]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" refId="ref3811" refString="Bauhin, G. (1623) Pinax Theatri Botanici. L. Regis, Basel, 522 pp." type="book" year="1623">Bauhin 1623</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D53A8AFBFD5EFE2E" author="Morison, R." box="[573,731,482,509]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" refId="ref5759" refString="Morison, R. (1680) Plantarum Historiae Universalis Oxoniensis, vol. 2. Theatro Sheldoniano, Oxford, 617 pp. + 126 plates." type="book" year="1680">Morison 1680</bibRefCitation>
) were given as references. The following three illustrations were directly or indirectly cited, and thus comprise original material: figure on the left (“ 
<taxonomicName id="93BA4D4BFFF0FFE2D326891EFABCFDF3" box="[1057,1337,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Persicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pusilla" subSpecies="repens">
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D326891EFABCFDF3" box="[1057,1337,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Persicaria pusilla repens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”) on page 
<quantity id="93429B2DFFF0FFE2D78F8933FF54FD97" box="[136,209,554,580]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1328399999999998" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="446.0">446 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D7DE8933FE09FD96" author="Johnson, T." box="[217,396,554,581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" refId="ref5090" refString="Johnson, T. (1633) The Herball, very much enlarged and amended. A. Islip, J. Norton &amp; R. Whitakers, London, 1630 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 121658" type="book" year="1633">Johnson (1633)</bibRefCitation>
; figure on the lower-left (“ 
<taxonomicName id="93BA4D4BFFF0FFE2D5C78932FC5BFD97" box="[704,990,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Persicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pusilla" subSpecies="repens">
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D5C78932FC5BFD97" box="[704,990,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Persicaria pusilla repens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”) on page 
<quantity id="93429B2DFFF0FFE2D3598933FB22FD97" box="[1118,1191,554,581]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.17678" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="857.0">857 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D3A88933FAF0FD96" author="Parkinson, J." box="[1199,1397,554,581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" refId="ref5863" refString="Parkinson, J. (1640) Theatrum Botanicum. Th. Cotes, London, 1755 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 152383" type="book" year="1640">Parkinson (1640)</bibRefCitation>
; and figure on the lower-left (“ 
<taxonomicName id="93BA4D4BFFF0FFE2D6AE8956FDECFDBB" authorityName="Opiz, Seznam Rostlin Kveteny Ceske" authorityYear="1852" baseAuthorityName="Huds." box="[425,617,591,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Persicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D6AE8956FDECFDBB" box="[425,617,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Persicaria minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”) of plate 29 of section 
<quantity id="93429B2DFFF0FFE2D47E8957FC21FDBB" box="[889,932,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D4AC8957FBDBFDBA" author="Morison, R." box="[939,1118,590,617]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" refId="ref5759" refString="Morison, R. (1680) Plantarum Historiae Universalis Oxoniensis, vol. 2. Theatro Sheldoniano, Oxford, 617 pp. + 126 plates." type="book" year="1680">Morison (1680)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="540536C8FFF0FFE2D7BA896AFD40FCCE" blockId="7.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">
No original specimens could be located for the name 
<taxonomicName id="93BA4D4BFFF0FFE2D411896AFCF0FD5F" baseAuthorityName="Hudson" baseAuthorityYear="1762" box="[790,885,627,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Polygonum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minus">
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D411896AFCF0FD5F" box="[790,885,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">P. minus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the majority of William Hudson’s herbarium was destroyed by fire prior to his death (Fred Rumsey, pers. comm., 
<date id="20041008FFF0FFE2D451898FFB89FD63" box="[854,1036,662,688]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" value="2020-08-19">19 August 2020</date>
), and the remainder of his specimens are kept at BM and LINN (
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D6CE89A3FD68FD06" author="Lanjouw, J. &amp; Stafleu, F. A." box="[457,749,698,725]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" refId="ref5441" refString="Lanjouw, J. &amp; Stafleu, F. A. (1957) Index Herbariorum, part II (2). International Association for Plant Taxonomy, Utrecht, 121 pp." type="book" year="1957">Lanjouw &amp; Stafleu 1957</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, in accordance with Arts. 9.3 and 9.4 of the ICN, we designate here as 
<typeStatus id="8B01886AFFF0FFE2D65E89C7FE45FD2B" box="[345,448,734,760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">lectotype</typeStatus>
the best among the original illustrations, 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D4AE89C6FC55FD2B" box="[937,976,735,760]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">viz.</emphasis>
the figure on the lower-left (“ 
<taxonomicName id="93BA4D4BFFF0FFE2D23289C6FF4EFCCF" authorityName="Opiz, Seznam Rostlin Kveteny Ceske" authorityYear="1852" baseAuthorityName="Huds." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Persicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D23289C6FF4EFCCF" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Persicaria minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”) of plate 29 of section 
<quantity id="93429B2DFFF0FFE2D6DC881BFD83FCCF" box="[475,518,770,797]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="302B4B39FFF0FFE2D50A881BFD45FCCE" author="Morison, R." box="[525,704,770,797]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" refId="ref5759" refString="Morison, R. (1680) Plantarum Historiae Universalis Oxoniensis, vol. 2. Theatro Sheldoniano, Oxford, 617 pp. + 126 plates." type="book" year="1680">Morison (1680)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="540536C8FFF0FFE2D7BA883FFBADFC7F" blockId="7.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">
Illustrations alone could be insufficient for the accurate application of species names in genera with complicated taxonomy, such as is the case for 
<taxonomicName id="93BA4D4BFFF0FFE2D51F8852FD0BFCB7" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[536,654,843,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Persicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D51F8852FD0BFCB7" box="[536,654,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Persicaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, Morison’s illustration is not sufficient for the unambiguous application of the name 
<taxonomicName id="93BA4D4BFFF0FFE2D69A8877FDECFC5B" baseAuthorityName="Hudson" baseAuthorityYear="1762" box="[413,617,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Polygonum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minus">
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D69A8877FDECFC5B" box="[413,617,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">Polygonum minus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, in accordance with Art. 9.9 of the ICN, we designate here as epitype a complete and well-preserved specimen, 
<emphasis id="66CEEADAFFF0FFE2D5B0888AFD58FC7F" box="[695,733,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="67">viz.</emphasis>
BM barcode BM001072687.
</paragraph>
